Subject: RE: [VB] Air shocks on a bus?

When I bought this truck the PO was trying to make a CA cruiser out of it. The
rear spring plates were re-adjusted to lower the rear and there were shorty
air shocks installed. (You don't even want to know what he did to lower the
front!). Anyway, when I restored stock height on the spring plates and put
back in standard shocks I came up with a pair of used air shocks. Free to
anyone who wants to pay the postage.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34 PICT-3
71 Trike 1776cc Dual T-4 34 PDSIT-3
VolksAir 1585cc 31 PICT
http://mywebpage.netscape.com/alphahr/case.html
Ray, Kent WA
